Status outcome object (success or error)

detaileddescription.para: The Status object is an object holding the outcome of an operation. The outcome is represented as a StatusCode, either success (StatusCode::OK) or an error (any other of the StatusCode enumeration values).
Additionally, if an error occurred, a specific error message is generally attached.
